<br>
To the point, I'd like to hear some suggestions for gear upgrades now that the bazaar has gone live. I was never a great trader/buyer/seller, but with the bazaar, I've managed to do a few quick upgrades rather easily, so it would be feasible to shoot for higher standards.<br>
<br>
My guild is ToV capable, we're on dragon faction and many of us have full or near full skyshrine armor. We do not yet do NToV. We have killed Vindicator. Just a little heads up as to what my guild is capable of, to assist in throwing up items that are within, or nearly within my grasp due to my guild's abilities.<br>
<br>
The robe can be upgraded as soon as we get a SS robe to drop (not that I'm overly thrilled, I've never been a big fan of flaming neon apothic). I am overboard on int, I have 255, with 14 to spare, and a Bracelet of comprehension (15int, +6 to all saves) on a wrist, so I can ditch that. I prefer to have 255 because we do not always have a KEI chanter available at raids. I know my HP total is way low, so my mod rod skills for being a mana battery of sorts are not that great. My mana pool is most likely pitiful as well. I do not like sacraficing mana for other stats, though I guess technically in the long run that's better off. I've always gone for stats in this order, int, mana, hp, resists, sta... but I realize that might be a bit out of order. I'm not a huge fan of the whole mana battery idea, and prefer a dd/support approach with mana being a nice bonus but I dislike doing the rod thing. I will if I have to however.<br>
<br>
Can anyone give me some good suggestions for equipment that might help me up my HP total without sacraficing too much mana, or just gear that can up my mana total along with hp? Magelo profile on the sig, ignore the &quot;resists&quot; profiles, they aren't updated. <p><br><br><img src="http://ruconfused.com/morph.gif" border="0"><br>
